@META
dir: helm
updated: 2026-03-18
files: 15
stack: Helm 3, Kubernetes

@EXPORTS
ucebnice/: Helm chart — complete K8s deployment for the app
ucebnice/templates/deployment.yaml: Deployment — Next.js app container
ucebnice/templates/service.yaml: Service — ClusterIP service
ucebnice/templates/ingress.yaml: Ingress — NGINX ingress with TLS
ucebnice/templates/configmap.yaml: ConfigMap — non-secret config
ucebnice/templates/secret.yaml: Secret — sensitive env vars
ucebnice/templates/hpa.yaml: HPA — horizontal pod autoscaler
ucebnice/templates/pdb.yaml: PDB — pod disruption budget
ucebnice/templates/serviceaccount.yaml: ServiceAccount — pod identity
ucebnice/templates/postgres-statefulset.yaml: StatefulSet — PostgreSQL database
ucebnice/templates/postgres-service.yaml: Service — PostgreSQL ClusterIP
ucebnice/templates/postgres-secret.yaml: Secret — DB credentials
ucebnice/templates/data-pvc.yaml: PVC — persistent volume for data
ucebnice/templates/_helpers.tpl: helpers — Helm template helpers

@PROCESSES
Deploy: helm upgrade --install ucebnice ./helm/ucebnice -f values-{env}.yaml

@DEPENDENCIES
internal: argocd/ (references this chart)
external: Kubernetes 1.25+, NGINX Ingress Controller

@STANDARDS
- PostgreSQL deployed as StatefulSet alongside app
- HPA scales 2-10 replicas based on CPU/memory
- PDB ensures minimum availability during rollouts
